{"word":"κερδίων","slug":"κερδίων","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>κερδίων</b></el> <br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:Comparative'>comp.</a> with no Posit. in use, formed from <a href='S:κέρδος'><el>κέρδος</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>more profitable</i>, <b><a href='S:Homer'>Hom.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><el>κέρδιστος, η, ον</el>, <a href='S:Superlative'>Sup.</a> <i>most cunning</i> or <i>crafty</i>, <b><a href='S:Iliad'>Il.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b>of things, <i>most profitable</i>, <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}